          <h2>World — seed from terrain</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The blocks come first. Islands, symmetry, and buildability seed the team count, the spawn
           positions, and where regions may sit — so no step starts blank.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        A new map (the <code>thunder_blank</code> class) is a world with blocks but no
        <code>map.xml</code>. The read-side analyses run on that terrain and bridge the physical world to
        the logical intent. Crucially, the <strong>y=0 footprint is the void-filter substrate</strong>:
        every column with a surface block is automatically buildable, so the terrain itself <em>is</em> the
        build area and <em>no region rows are generated for it</em>. Island count and the detected symmetry
        seed the team count and where each side drops its spawn.
      </p>

