        <p>Define team 0 once — symmetry orbit fills the rest, the spawn protection is auto-wired.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        In the intent model a team's <em>spawn point</em> and its <em>protection zone</em> are one unit,
        defined once for the authored team (team 0 · Blue). The system uses the confirmed
        <code>rot_90</code> symmetry to rotate that unit onto the other three orbit positions, then
        auto-wires the <code>enter = only-&lt;team&gt;</code> filter on each protection zone. You never touch
        the region / filter graph. This fixes the old editor's split, where a spawn and its protection
        lived under different tree branches.
      </p>

