    <section class="ds-section" id="build">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">02</p>
          <h2>Build</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The terrain is already buildable. You draw only the bridges over the void — the system unions
           them and enforces the rest.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        PGM's void filter (<code>block = not(void)</code> on the <em>negative</em> of the build group) makes
        every column that has a surface block automatically editable, so the islands' terrain <strong>is</strong>
        the build area with no region rows generated for it. <code>BuildIntent.Areas</code> are therefore only
        the <em>over-void extensions</em> — the bridges and platforms you want buildable across the gaps between
        islands. Set the max build height, mark the bridges, and the generator unions them and applies the void
        filter to the complement. Inner cut-outs (holes) are supported as a <code>complement</code>.
      </p>

      <article class="ds-example">
        <div class="ds-example-label">Build workspace — bridges + live buildability overlay</div>
        <div class="ds-workspace-frame">
          <div class="workspace">

            <div class="workspace-sidebar">
              <div class="workspace-scroll">
                <section class="panel-section">
                  <div class="section-header section-header--ruled"><h2 class="section-title">Build Height</h2></div>
                  <div class="section-body">
                    <div class="field">
                      <label class="field-label">Max build height</label>
                      <input class="field-input" type="number" value="25"/>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </section>
                <section class="panel-section">
