      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        The author defines a single wool: its colour, the block where it spawns, the room region around it, and
        its monuments. Monument count is pre-filled from the team count — on a four-team map every <em>other</em>
        team must capture it, so <strong>N − 1 = 3 monuments per wool</strong>. Orbit-fill then rotates the unit
        through the remaining three teams, and the system auto-wires room defense, room build/break, and monument
        capture from the wiring templates. Coordinate flooring is PGM-grounded: the wool <code>&lt;location&gt;</code>
