    <!-- ════════════════════════ PRINCIPLES ════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="ds-section" id="principles">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">08</p>
          <h2>Principles</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The rules that keep this experience simple. Full contract lives in
           <code>docs/contracts/new-map-authoring.md</code>.</p>
      </div>

      <table class="ds-rules-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Do</th><th>Don't</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>State intent — teams, spawns, build, wools. Intent is the source of truth.</td><td>Hand-edit the region / filter graph. Regions are a derived projection.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Define one authored unit per symmetry orbit; let orbit fill the rest.</td><td>Place every team's spawn / wool by hand on a symmetric map.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Correct intent anytime — regenerate is a free re-save (drops + recreates all rows).</td><td>Diff or patch generated regions to “fix” a change.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Let templates union the regions a filter needs and wire them.</td><td>Build union / complement structure by hand to wire a filter.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Draw only over-void bridges in Build; the terrain is auto-buildable.</td><td>Trace the islands as build rectangles — the void filter covers them.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Floor a coordinate iff PGM won't (wool location yes, monument block no).</td><td>Normalize every coordinate blindly.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gate export on traversability; loop back to Build to bridge gaps.</td><td>Export a valid-but-unplayable map with isolated islands.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Keep the full region tree as a read-only inspection surface.</td><td>Make the data-model tree the authoring surface.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="ds-subsection" style="margin-top:var(--space-6)">
        <h3>The mirror property</h3>
        <p class="ds-theming-note">
          Generation and categorization are inverses. The strongest correctness test isn't that the output is
          <em>valid</em> — it's that <code>DeriveFacets(generate(intent))</code> recovers the intent's classification:
          the spawn protection reads back as <code>spawn/protection</code>, the wool room as <code>wool/room</code>,
          the build union as <code>build</code>, the monuments as <code>wool/monument</code>. A generated map that
          round-trips through the codec and reads back as the intent that produced it is correct by construction —
          which is exactly why a blank map like <code>thunder_blank</code> can be authored to a valid export.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</div>

</div>
